==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nub
<hw>Nub</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Knob</er>.]</ety> <def>To push; to nudge; also, to beckon.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nub</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nub
<hw>Nub</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A jag, or snag; a knob; a protuberance;
also, the point or gist, as of a story.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nubbin</ent>⟦br⟧
